                <p><span>5.3 Customers that match numbers from the Winning Numbers drawn can win in the Raffle Draw and the Ball Draw.</span></p>
                <p><span>5.4 In the Ball Draw, Customers can only win in one Prize category per single Entry but shall be entitled to receive the Prize for the highest Prize category won (i.e., if You are a Match Five winner, You will only receive the Match Five Prize. You will not receive a Match Four, Match Three, Match Two and Match One Prize).</span></p>
                <p><span>5.5 Prizes will be rounded to the nearest AED 1 (One Dirham).</span></p>
                <p><span>5.6 All Prize winners will be notified by email, in-Platform messages, and, where relevant, push notifications.</span></p>
                <p><span>5.7 All winnings will be paid directly into Your Winning Balance.</span></p>
                <p><span>5.8 For non-UAE national winners, federal and jurisdictional income taxes may apply to any monetary Prize.</span></p>
                <p><span>5.9 At Our sole discretion, We may decide to pay out the Match 6 Grand Prize in a lump sum, regular installments, or a combination of both.</span></p>
                <h4>6. Payment of Prizes</h4>
                <p><span>6.1 Before the payment of a Prize, the Customer may be validated according to Win &amp; Win Customer validation procedures (KYC), including screening against the International Embargoed and Sanctions List. Our decision as to the validity of an Entry is final and binding.</span></p>
                <p><span>6.2 In addition, before a Prize is paid, you may be required to provide:</span></p>
                <p><span>6.2.1 full identification documentation; and/or</span></p>
                <p><span>6.2.2 a statutory declaration of ownership, entitlement, and compliance with relevant laws.</span></p>
                <p><span>6.3 We will only pay a Prize based on the official Winning Numbers of the relevant Draw recorded in line with Win &amp; Win Rules and will not pay a Prize based on results recorded elsewhere.</span></p>
                <p><span>6.4 Subject to verification of identity, proof of age, and Entry validation:</span></p>
                <p><span>6.5 Match Five and Match Six (Grand Prize) Prizes must be claimed in person in the UAE. Payment will be made (at Our discretion) by cheque or bank transfer to a UAE bank account.</span></p>
                <p><span>6.6 Payment of the Prize to the Claimant (or their authorized representative) shall fully and effectively discharge Win &amp; Win, its officers, employees, representatives, contractors, and any person or firm authorized by Us to pay Prizes from any further liability for payment of that Prize.</span></p>
                <p><span>6.7 We reserve the right to:</span></p>
                <p><span>6.7.1 withhold a Prize until We are satisfied that an Entry is valid and the Claimant is lawfully entitled to payment of a Prize.</span></p>
                <p><span>6.7.2 request proof of entitlement to a Prize (including, without limitation, identification information, proof of identity, residency, or location when Entering Draws and capacity to claim).</span></p>
                <p><span>6.7.3 invite a court to decide who a Prize should be paid to and make payment to the court.</span></p>
                <p><span>6.7.4 declare an Entry invalid (and will not, therefore, be obliged to pay any Prize) if:</span></p>
                
                <ol style="padding-left: 80px;">
                   <li style="list-style:decimal !important;">We reasonably believe that the Claimant is not the holder of the relevant Account or that the information provided by the Claimant is incomplete or has been altered or tampered with.</li>
                   <li style="list-style:decimal !important;">the Entry has been tampered with in whole or in part or fails to pass our validation and security tests; or</li>
                   <li style="list-style:decimal !important;">the Entry is defective, in whole or in part.</li>
                </ol>
                
                <p><span>6.8 We reserve the right to refuse and will not be liable to pay a Customer a Prize if:</span></p>
                <ol style="padding-left: 80px;">
                   <li style="list-style:decimal !important;"><span>the Customer does not meet the eligibility criteria or</span></li>
                   <li style="list-style:decimal !important;"><span>You are unable or fail to supply the necessary identification documentation when claiming a Prize.</span></li>
                   <li style="list-style:decimal !important;"><span>If a Prize is paid to anyone who does not meet such eligibility criteria, that person will be obliged to repay the Prize immediately upon Our request. We reserve the right to recover any incorrectly paid Prize.</span></li>
                </ol>
                <p><span>6.9 We will not be responsible or liable to any person claiming a Prize that has been paid to a person who assumed the identity of the relevant Account Holder.</span></p>
                <p><span>6.10 Under no circumstances will interest be payable on any Prize.</span></p>
                <p><span>6.11 Prizes will be paid in full only to the registered holder of the Account with the winning Entry, unless You are a person with a legal, physical or other disability and are claiming a Prize, where, in these circumstances, we may pay the Prize to Your authorized representative.</span></p>
                <p><span>6.12 In the event of the death of a Claimant, a person can claim on behalf of such deceased Claimant’s estate where they can prove, to Our satisfaction, that they are entitled to make such a claim (for example, by providing a grant of probate).</span></p>
                <p><span>6.13 All cash Prizes will be paid in United Arab Emirates Dirhams in the amount advised by the Us as the final amount payable for that winning Entry.</span></p>
                <p><span>6.14 Due to anti-money laundering rules and regulations, Match Six (Grand Prize) Prizes will only be paid into a UAE bank account (an Authorised Financial Institution can assist with account opening if required).</span></p>
                <p><span>6.15 We disclaim all liability, including any express or implied warranties, whether oral or written to any Syndicate Members. By Entering Games, you acknowledge that we have made no representation that We shall be responsible for or have any liability for any purported claim from a Syndicate Member. To avoid doubt, we will only be liable for any valid claim by the registered account holder with the winning Entry.</span></p>
                <p><span>6.16 Where You Enter with the intent of sharing a Prize with Syndicate Members, you are:</span></p>
                <p><span>6.16.1 deemed to be the Customer for these Rules; and</span></p>
                <p><span>6.16.2 are not acting as Our agent for that purpose, and We shall not be:</span></p>
                <ul type="disc">
                   <li>liable for the payment of any Prize to any Syndicate Member other than a Prize emanating from a winning Entry which is payable only to the registered holder of the Account with such winning Entry; and</li>
                   <li><span>bound by any agreement between the registered holder of the Account and any Syndicate Member.</span></li>
                </ul>
                <h4>7. Winners’ Information</h4>
                <p><span>7.1 By participating in the Draw, you accept that We may disclose relevant personal details about You. We may also, if required by law or under the terms of Our Grand Prize insurance, provide a third party with Your details and the details of any Prize claimed by You or on Your behalf or paid to You.</span></p>
                <h4>8. Draw Postponement</h4>
                <p><span>8.1 If Win &amp; Win deems it reasonable, we may delay a Draw for as long as We believe it to be appropriate in the circumstances. In these instances, Customers will be permitted to Enter the Draw beyond the regular cut-off times for that Draw.</span></p>
                <h4>9, Limitation of Liability</h4>
                <p><span>9.1 Our only obligation is to pay the Prizes won in any Draw to the rightful owners of winning Entries. In many circumstances, we will not be liable for any loss other than the non-payment of a Prize to the rightful owners of winning Entries.</span></p>
                <p><span>9.2 We shall not in any circumstances be liable for any loss, direct or consequential, or damage incurred by any Customer or any other person arising from the participation by any person in the Draw. But without prejudice to the generality of this rule, we shall not be liable to any person for:</span></p>
                <p><span>a) events beyond Our reasonable control and expectations (for example, without limitation, war, strike, lockout, industrial action, fire, flood, drought, power cut, and failure or obstruction of any network, broadcasting, or telecommunications service).</span></p>
                <p><span>b) the failure or destruction of, or damage to, all or part of the Central Computer System, Our records, or any third party.</span></p>
                <p><span>c) any mistakes caused by all or part of the Central Computer System, our records, or any third party.</span></p>
                <p><span>d) delays, losses, mistakes, or omissions in or made by the banking system.</span></p>
                <p><span>e) any other action or event which prevents or hinders the issue of a valid Entry (including without limitation the failure of the Platform to display correctly on any device used to view it).</span></p>
                <p><span>9.3 Nothing in these Rules excludes or limits (a) any person’s liability (i) for fraud; or (ii) for death or personal injury caused by the breach of any duty that person may have to take reasonable care or exercise reasonable skill; or (b) any other liability which cannot lawfully be excluded or limited.</span></p>
                <h4>10. General</h4>
                <p><span>10.1 The reasonable exercise by Us of any discretion provided by these Rules, including concerning the determination of a winning Entry or payment of a Prize, will be final and binding unless otherwise provided by law.</span></p>
                <p><span>10.2 If a dispute arises, we may withhold payment of a Prize and make an equivalent payment in court until it has been resolved.</span></p>
                <p><span>10.3 If any provision (or part of a provision) in any of these Rules is decided by a court of competent jurisdiction to be void and unenforceable, that decision will only affect the particular condition (or part of the provision). It will not make the other provisions void or unenforceable.</span></p>
                <p><span>10.4 You may not assign or otherwise transfer (in whole or part) Your rights and obligations under these Rules, including, for the avoidance of doubt, the right to a Prize. Any assignment or transfer by You will be null and void. We may assign or transfer Our rights and obligations under these Rules in whole or part to any third party at Our sole discretion.</span></p>
                <p><span>10.5 Except if We assign or transfer Our rights and obligations under these Rules, a person who is not a party to these Rules has no rights or otherwise to enforce any provision.</span></p>
                <p><span>10.6 We may amend these Rules from time to time. Such amendments, modifications, or changes will be applicable and contractually binding with effect from the date of their publication on the Platform or on notification to You that changes have taken place, whichever is sooner and will apply to Entries made after the date on which the changes become effective, and Entries made before that date if reasonable in the circumstances. If We change these Rules, You will be notified the next time You access Your Account.</span></p>
                <h4>11. Law</h4>
                <p><span>11.1 The relevant law for these Rules is the laws of the UAE, and any legal proceedings will be heard in the UAE Courts.</span></p>
